{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fsr"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode\/fsr"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/viewportscaling3dmode\/fsr"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution 1.0 upscaling for the viewport’s 3D buffer. The amount of scaling can be set using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". Values less than "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be result in the viewport being upscaled using FSR. Values greater than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" are not supported and bilinear downsampling will be used instead. A value of "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" disables scaling."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode"]]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fsr","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","symbolKind":"case","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15RenderingServerC21ViewportScaling3DModeO3fsryA2EmF","title":"RenderingServer.ViewportScaling3DMode.fsr"},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text",